"""
omor_4h_system.py
=================
Pair-agnostic replication of the Omor 4H Sweep Entry Framework.

SYSTEM RULES (as described)
----------------------------
Signal fires on bar i, entry at open of bar i+1.

LONG conditions (all must be true on bar i):
  1. Sweep:        low[i]  < low[i-1]                              (swept prior low)
  2. Close 70%:    close   >= ((high - low) * 0.70) + low          (bullish close)
  3. MA200 bias:   close   > MA(200) × 0.995                       (soft — within 0.5% below allowed)
  4. MA50 tap:     close   > MA(50)                                 (recovered above MA50)
  5. ADX:          ADX(14) > threshold                              (trending, not ranging)

SHORT conditions (mirror of long):
  1. Sweep:        high[i] > high[i-1]
  2. Close 70%:    close   <= high - ((high - low) * 0.70)
  3. MA200 bias:   close   < MA(200) × 1.005                       (soft — within 0.5% above allowed)
  4. MA50 tap:     close   < MA(50)
  5. ADX:          ADX(14) > threshold

Removed as over-filters (kept as diagnostic columns only):
  - MA50 dist:   abs(low/high − MA50) <= ATR(14)   — redundant; rejects large sweep candles
  - ADR cap:     (high − low) <= 0.75 × ADR(5)     — specifically rejects the core sweep setup

Trade execution:
  Entry  = open[i+1]
  SL     = low[i]  (long) | high[i] (short)
  TP     = entry + (entry - SL) * 1.9   (long)
           entry - (SL - entry) * 1.9   (short)

OANDA London 4H sessions only: 02:00, 06:00, 10:00, 14:00, 18:00
Overnight candle (22:00) excluded due to low volatility.

USAGE
-----
  from omor_4h_system import build_4h_candles, generate_signals, backtest

  # Start from 1H OHLCV data (UTC-aware DatetimeIndex)
  df_4h    = build_4h_candles(df_1h)
  df_sig   = generate_signals(df_4h)
  trades, summary = backtest(df_4h)
  print(summary)
"""

